text: Lemazy () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Lemazinsky Selsoviet, Duvansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 531 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 45 km from Mesyagutovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Duvansky District
title: Lemazy
